<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3953] Surefire plugin executes unit tests twice</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3953</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3909&quot; title=&quot;Maven Failsafe plugin may report SUCCESS on failed tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-3909&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-3909&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the unit tests are executed twice. There are now two executions defined for the Surefire plugin: &lt;tt&gt;unit-tests&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;integration-tests&lt;/tt&gt;. In addition, there is a default execution called &lt;tt&gt;default-test&lt;/tt&gt;. This leads to the unit tests to be executed twice. Either renaming unit-tests to default-test or skipping default-test would fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
