                            <comment id="15296191" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 23 May 2016 10:10:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user mxm opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2019&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2019&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3953&quot; title=&quot;Surefire plugin executes unit tests twice&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-3953&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-3953&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; rename unit-tests execution to default-test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    After 38698c0b101cbb48f8c10adf4060983ac07e2f4b, there are now two&lt;br/&gt;
    executions defined for the Surefire plugin: unit-tests and&lt;br/&gt;
    integration-tests. In addition, there is an implicit default execution&lt;br/&gt;
    called default-test. This leads to the unit tests to be executed&lt;br/&gt;
    twice. This renames unit-tests to default-test to prevent duplicate&lt;br/&gt;
    execution.&lt;/p&gt;

